  "texts": [
    "ML models such as Support Vector Machines (SVMs) and hidden Markov models have been used for BioNER.",
    "Although ML techniques perform better than other traditional methods, they require a large amount of manually annotated training data [38].",
    "Pre-trained language models such as Bio-BERT can be fine-tuned to easily perform BioNER without needing a large amount of training data.",
    "BERN2, a BioNER tool reported in 2022, not only supports NER, but also allows named entity normalization (NEN).",
    "NEN allows mapping recognised named entities to a common or canonical form ensuring uniform representation of named entities."
  ],
